Document: DPITexture
Path: godot/classes/class_dpitexture.rst
Summary: This section describes the methods available for the DPITexture class in Godot Engine.

Method: create_from_string(source: String, scale: float = 1.0, saturation: float = 1.0, color_map: Dictionary = {}) → RID |static|
Creates a DPITexture from a string. The string is interpreted as a series of commands to draw shapes. The scale parameter controls the resolution of the generated texture. Saturation affects the color intensity. The color_map allows remapping of colors in the source string.

Method: get_scaled_rid() → RID |const|
Returns the RID of the scaled texture. This is the texture that is actually rendered and displayed.

Method: get_source() → String |const|
Returns the source string used to create the DPITexture.

Method: set_size_override(size: Vector2i) → void
Overrides the default size of the DPITexture. This can be used to force a specific resolution for the texture, independent of the source string or scale.

Method: set_source(source: String) → void
Sets a new source string for the DPITexture. This will cause the texture to be regenerated based on the new string.
