Document: DPITexture
Path: godot/classes/class_dpitexture.rst
Summary: This section describes the methods available for the DPITexture class in Godot Engine, including creating textures from strings, getting scaled RIDs, retrieving source code, and setting size overrides or source code.

Method: create_from_string(source: String, scale: float = 1.0, saturation: float = 1.0, color_map: Dictionary = {}) -> DPITexture |static|
Creates a new DPITexture and initializes it by allocating and setting the SVG data to source.

Method: get_scaled_rid() -> RID |const|
Returns the RID of the texture rasterized to match the oversampling of the currently drawn canvas item.

Method: get_source() -> String |const|
Returns this SVG texture's source code.

Method: set_size_override(size: Vector2i) -> void
Resizes the texture to the specified dimensions.

Method: set_source(source: String) -> void
Sets this SVG texture's source code.